                            <comment id="12931543" author="xuefuz" created="Fri, 12 Nov 2010 22:16:32 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Here is the behavior that Pig is taking:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;1. If JVM property &quot;mapred.output.compress&quot; is set to &quot;true&quot;, then the output is always compressed (regardless of the output file extension).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. If the JVM property &quot;mapred.output.compress&quot; is not set or is set to &quot;false&quot;, then whether pig output is compressed depends on the given file extension: if the extension is .bz or .bz2, then bzip compression will be used. If the extension is gz, then gzip compression will be used. In all other cases, no compression will be performed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;3. When JVM property &quot;mapred.output.compress&quot; is set to &quot;true&quot;, then another property, &quot;mapred.output.compress.codec&quot; must also be set. Otherwise, exception will be thrown.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
